cat > .claude/skills/create-2gp-version/SKILL.md << 'SKILL'
---
name: create-2gp-version
description: Create and optionally promote a 2GP package version.
allowed-tools: Bash, Read
---

# Steps
1. Validate source deploys cleanly:
   `sf project deploy start --dry-run --target-org <scratch>`
2. Run full test suite via `run-apex-tests` skill
3. Create package version:
   `sf package version create -p <packageAlias> -w 30 --code-coverage --installation-key-bypass`
4. Verify version created:
   `sf package version list --released-versions-only --json`
5. If promoting: `sf package version promote -p <subscriberPackageVersionId>`
6. Return JSON: `{status, subscriberPackageVersionId, coveragePercent, warnings[]}`

# Guards
- Never promote without 75%+ code coverage
- Verify ancestor version is correct for upgrade path
- Test install in fresh scratch org before promoting
SKILL

cat > .claude/skills/run-apex-tests/SKILL.md << 'SKILL'
---
name: run-apex-tests
description: Run Apex tests and return coverage summary.
allowed-tools: Bash, Read
---

# Steps
1. Run tests:
   `sf apex run test --test-level RunLocalTests --code-coverage --result-format json --wait 10`
2. Parse results and return:
   `{status, coveragePercent, failures:[{class,method,message}], slowTests:[{class,time}]}`
3. If failures exist, include stack traces
4. Flag any class below 75% individual coverage

# Options
- `--class-names <name>` for single class testing
- `--suite-names <suite>` for test suite execution
