cat > .claude/skills/generate-test-factory/SKILL.md << 'SKILL'
---
name: generate-test-factory
description: Generate or update TestDataFactory class with methods for project sObjects.
allowed-tools: Bash, Read, Write
---

# Steps
1. Scan `force-app/` for custom objects and standard object usage
2. Check if `TestDataFactory.cls` exists — update if so, create if not
3. For each sObject found, generate a `create<ObjectName>()` method that:
   - Sets all required fields with sensible defaults
   - Accepts optional parameter overrides via Map<String,Object>
   - Returns the inserted record
4. Include a `createBulk<ObjectName>(Integer count)` variant for bulk testing
5. Class must use `@isTest` visibility and `with sharing`

# Template Pattern
```apex
public with sharing class TestDataFactory {
    public static Account createAccount(Map<String,Object> overrides) {
        Account a = new Account(Name = 'Test Account');
        for (String field : overrides.keySet()) {
            a.put(field, overrides.get(field));
        }
        insert a;
        return a;
    }
}
```
SKILL

