cat > .claude/skills/architect/SKILL.md << 'SKILL'
---
name: architect
description: Solution architecture advisor for Salesforce projects. Covers data model, trigger framework, integrations, governor limits, security architecture, and package design.
allowed-tools: Read, Bash
---

# Capabilities

## Data Model Design
- Evaluate lookup vs master-detail relationships (cascade delete, rollups, sharing)
- Recommend junction objects for many-to-many
- Custom Metadata Types for static config; Hierarchy Custom Settings for org/profile overrides
- Big Objects for high-volume archival (100M+ records)
- External Objects with Salesforce Connect for external data

## Trigger Framework (Recommended: Kevin O'Hara Pattern)
- One trigger per object, delegates to handler class
- Handler extends TriggerHandler base class
- Override context methods: beforeInsert, afterUpdate, etc.
- Built-in recursion prevention via static flags
- Structure:
  ```
  triggers/   → AccountTrigger.trigger (one-liner delegation)
  classes/    → AccountTriggerHandler.cls extends TriggerHandler
  classes/    → TriggerHandler.cls (base class)
  ```
- Reference: github.com/kevinohara80/sfdc-trigger-framework

## Integration Patterns
- Platform Events: async event-driven (pub/sub, replay support)
- Change Data Capture (CDC): real-time data change streaming
- REST callouts: use Named Credentials (never hardcode endpoints)
- Composite API: batch multiple operations in single request
- Outbound Messages: legacy — avoid for new development

## Governor Limits Planning
- 100 SOQL queries per transaction → batch + aggregate queries
- 150 DML statements per transaction → collect and bulkify
- 6MB heap (sync) / 12MB heap (async) → stream large data sets
- 10-second CPU time → offload to async (Queueable, Batch)
- Callout limits: 100 per transaction, 120s total timeout

## Security Architecture
- Sharing model: OWD → Role Hierarchy → Sharing Rules → Manual/Apex Sharing
- Permission Sets over Profiles for granular access
- Custom Permissions for feature flags
- Shield Platform Encryption for sensitive fields
- Event Monitoring for audit trails

## Package Dependency Design
- Base package: shared objects, utilities, trigger framework
- Feature packages: depend on base, independent of each other
- Keep dependency graph shallow (max 2 levels deep)
SKILL

