cat > .claude/mcp.md << 'MCP'
# MCP — Salesforce DX MCP Server

This project uses the official `@salesforce/mcp` server (Beta).
Config: `.mcp.json` at project root.

## Available Toolsets
- `orgs` — manage authorized orgs (list, open, display)
- `metadata` — deploy, retrieve, list metadata
- `data` — run SOQL queries, manage records
- `users` — assign permission sets, manage users
- `testing` — run Apex tests, agent tests
- `code-analysis` — Salesforce Code Analyzer (static analysis)
- `lwc-experts` — LWC development guidance, best practices, Figma-to-LWC

## Key Tools
- `run_soql_query` — run SOQL against connected org
- `run_apex_test` — execute Apex tests
- `run_code_analyzer` — static analysis for security/quality
- `assign_permission_set` — assign permsets to users
- `guide_lwc_best_practices` — LWC coding standards

## Usage
Tools are auto-available via MCP protocol. Use natural language:
- "Run all Apex tests in my scratch org"
- "Deploy the Account trigger to my scratch org"
- "Analyze my Apex code for security issues"

## Docs
- https://github.com/salesforcecli/mcp
- https://developer.salesforce.com/docs/atlas.en-us.sfdx_dev.meta/sfdx_dev/sfdx_dev_mcp.htm
MCP

