# ${name}

Salesforce 2GP project. AI-assisted development via \`.claude/\` intelligence layer.

## Quick Reference
- **Namespace:** ${namespace:-<not-set>}
- **Dev Hub:** ${devhub}
- **CLI:** \`sf\` (unified CLI only)
- **MCP:** Salesforce DX MCP Server (see \`.mcp.json\`)

## Agent Commands (manual invocation)
- \`code-review-agent\` — static analysis for Apex changes
- \`qa-agent\` — generate and run tests
- \`security-review-agent\` — AppExchange security audit
- \`learn-agent\` — explain what you just built (learn-by-doing)
- \`git-agent\` — worktree parallel development
- \`packaging-agent\` — 2GP version lifecycle
- \`research-agent\` — fetch docs and metadata
- \`doc-writer-agent\` — generate class/component documentation

## Checkpoints
- \`.claude/checkpoints.json\` — project milestone tracker (setup → dev → packaging → appexchange)
- View: \`jq '.phases.development.tasks[]' .claude/checkpoints.json\`

## Skills (auto-activated)
- \`architect\` — solution design guidance
- \`create-2gp-version\` — package version lifecycle
- \`run-apex-tests\` — test execution
- \`deploy-validate\` — deployment validation
- \`generate-test-factory\` — TestDataFactory scaffolding
- \`metadata-audit\` — deprecated metadata detection
- \`appexchange-research\` — competitor analysis

## Rules (always enforced)
- \`apex-standards\` — bulkify, no DML in loops, with sharing
- \`lwc-standards\` — @wire, SLDS, Jest, a11y
- \`security-rules\` — CRUD/FLS, SOQL injection, no secrets
- \`2gp-packaging\` — version, promote, dependencies
- \`cli-usage\` — sf CLI patterns
- \`source-tracking\` — source-driven workflow
EOF

# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
#  README.md
# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
cat > README.md << EOF
# ${name}

Salesforce 2GP managed package project.

## Setup

1. **Authenticate Dev Hub:**
   \`\`\`bash
   sf org login web --alias ${devhub} --set-default-dev-hub
   \`\`\`

2. **Create scratch org:**
   \`\`\`bash
   bash scripts/automation/scratch-org-setup.sh
   \`\`\`

3. **Deploy source:**
   \`\`\`bash
   sf project deploy start
   \`\`\`

4. **Run tests:**
   \`\`\`bash
   sf apex run test --test-level RunLocalTests --code-coverage
   \`\`\`

## Project Structure

\`\`\`
force-app/main/default/    Source metadata (Apex, LWC, objects, etc.)
.claude/                   AI intelligence layer (rules, skills, agents)
.mcp.json                  Salesforce DX MCP Server config
scripts/hooks/             Pre-commit and post-deploy hooks
scripts/automation/        Scratch org setup, test data generation
\`\`\`

## AI-Assisted Development

This project includes a \`.claude/\` directory with:
- **Rules** — enforced coding and security standards
- **Skills** — executable checklists for common tasks
- **Agents** — specialized sub-agents for code review, QA, security audit
- **Memory** — persistent project context

See \`CLAUDE.md\` for full reference.

## Security

- Secrets go in Named Credentials or CI variables — never in source
- Run \`security-review-agent\` before AppExchange submission
- Run \`sf scanner run --target force-app/\` for Code Analyzer compliance
EOF

